heaviest_rainfall.status: Today's storm ranked 7th for total rainfall with 23.46mm having fallen, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  8.3mm per hour fell at points during the storm which lasted 30.3 hours.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 7th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 30.3 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  23.46mm of rain fell in total.  The record duration for continuous rain was set on 09 November 2025, the storm lasted 144.8 hours with a total precipitation of 47.89mm and it reached 24.6mm per hour at times.
